.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-MANGLE 5 "2026-04-20" "shorewall-nft 1.10.0" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-mangle \- packet mark (mangle) rules for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I mangle
file defines rules that set packet marks or connection marks on matching
traffic.  Marks are used to implement policy-based routing, traffic shaping,
and quality-of-service classification.

The compiler processes this file together with
.I tcrules
and emits
.B meta mark set
and
.B ct mark set
rules in the
.B mangle
chain (nft priority
.BR \-150 ).

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/mangle
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
ACTION	yes	Mark action: MARK, CONNMARK, SAVE, RESTORE, or mark value
SOURCE	yes	Source zone:address or CIDR
DEST	yes	Destination zone:address or CIDR
PROTO	no	Protocol filter
DPORT	no	Destination port filter
SPORT	no	Source port filter
USER	no	User/group match
TEST	no	Connmark test expression
LENGTH	no	Packet length range
TOS	no	TOS/DSCP value
CONNBYTES	no	Conntrack bytes matched
HELPER	no	Conntrack helper match
HEADERS	no	IPv6 extension header match
PROBABILITY	no	Probabilistic mark (0.0\(en1.0)
DSCP	no	DSCP value to set
STATE	no	Connection state match
TIME	no	Time range
SWITCH	no	Runtime switch name
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Mark all HTTP/HTTPS traffic for QoS:
.RS
.nf
#ACTION  SOURCE  DEST  PROTO  DPORT
1        all     all   tcp    80,443
.fi
.RE
.PP
Save connection mark on new connections:
.RS
.nf
SAVE     all     all
.fi
.RE
.PP
Restore mark from connection on established traffic:
.RS
.nf
RESTORE  all     all
.fi
.RE

.SH NFSET / DNS TOKENS
The SOURCE and DEST columns accept
.BR nfset:<name> ,
.BR dns:<hostname> ,
and
.BR dnsr:<hostname>
tokens — see
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5)
and
.BR shorewall\-nft\-nfsets (5)
for the full grammar.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-nfsets (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-providers (5)

